text: On a dark desert highway Cool wind in my head One smell of colitas rising Up through the air Up ahead in the distance I saw a shimmering light My head grew heavy and my side grew dim I had to stop for the night There she stood in the doorway I heard the mission bell And I was thinking to myself This could be heaven And this could be Then she lit up a candle And she showed me the way There were voices down this corridor I thought I heard them say Welcome to the Hotel California Such a lovely place Such a lovely place That you love your face Ready a room at the Hotel California Any time of year Any time of year You can find it here Her mind is differently twisted She got the Mercedes Benz She got a lot of pretty, pretty boys She called friends How they dance in the courtyard Sweet summer sweat Some dance to remember to forget So I called up the Captain Please bring me my wine He said we haven't had that spirit here Since nineteen sixty nine And still those voices are calling from far away Wake you up in the middle of the night Just to hear them Say Welcome to the Hotel Californ California Such a lovely place Such a lovely place Such a lovely face They live in it at the backyard Hotel California What a nice surprise What a nice surprise In your alibi Mirrors on the ceiling They pick champagne on ice And she said we are out Just prisoners here of our own device And in the master's chambers They gathered for their feast They stab it with their stealing eyes But they just can't kill the beast Last thing I remember I was running for the door I had to find the passage Back to the place I wasn't forced Relax at the Magic Man We are programmed to see You can check out anytime you like But you can never leave.
